The paper discusses formal specification and reasoning on dynamic systems, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of linear time calculus theories suggests a focus on logic and formal methods, which is reflected in the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) category. The extension of IDP 3, a knowledge representation and reasoning system, suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and automated reasoning, which is reflected in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The mention of databases suggests a focus on data management and querying, which is reflected in the cs.DB (Databases) category. The mention of planning suggests a focus on automated planning and scheduling, which is reflected in the cs.PL (Programming Languages) category. Finally, the focus on dynamic systems suggests a focus on control theory and systems engineering, which is reflected in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
